Rating: 2
I made this as a straight pasta salad without the chicken, adding 1 Tbl. of lemon juice to make up for the missing chicken juices. All the vegetables make it nice and crunchy. I only had dried dillweed on hand so I used half as much as the recipe called for; I'd use more next time or plan ahead and buy fresh dill. The only other change I'd make is to use a large red onion, but I LOVE onions, cooked or raw! I didn't find the dressing oily; I made it in my blender, trickling the olive oil in, and the dressing stayed emulsified. I'd definitely make this again. Leftovers are great to bring to work for lunch.

Rating: 2
